OL,5, Fewer than half of people in England   
OL,6, and Wales have described themselves as 
OL,7, Christian for the first time, the 2021 
OL,8, census has revealed.                   
OL,10,FThe proportion of people who said they 
OL,11,Fwere Christian was 46.2%, down from    
OL,12,F59.3% in the last census in 2011.      
OL,14,FMeanwhile the number who said they had 
OL,15,Fno religion increased to 37.2% of the  
OL,16,Fpopulation, up from a quarter.         
OL,18,FAnd people identifying as Muslim rose  
OL,19,Ffrom 4.9% in 2011 to 6.5% last year    
